README.md
     1Ôćĺ# xxhash
     2Ôćĺ
     3Ôćĺ[![Go Reference](https://pkg.go.dev/badge/github.com/cespare/xxhash/v2.svg)](https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/cespare/xxhash/v2)
     4Ôćĺ[![Test](https://github.com/cespare/xxhash/actions/workflows/test.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/cespare/xxhash/actions/workflows/test.yml)
     5Ôćĺ
     6Ôćĺxxhash is a Go implementation of the 64-bit [xxHash] algorithm, XXH64. This is a
     7Ôćĺhigh-quality hashing algorithm that is much faster than anything in the Go
     8Ôćĺstandard library.
     9Ôćĺ
    10ÔćĺThis package provides a straightforward API:
    11Ôćĺ
    12Ôćĺ```
    13Ôćĺfunc Sum64(b []byte) uint64
    14Ôćĺfunc Sum64String(s string) uint64
    15Ôćĺtype Digest struct{ ... }
    16Ôćĺ    func New() *Digest
    17Ôćĺ```
    18Ôćĺ
    19ÔćĺThe `Digest` type implements hash.Hash64. Its key methods are:
    20Ôćĺ
    21Ôćĺ```
    22Ôćĺfunc (*Digest) Write([]byte) (int, error)
    23Ôćĺfunc (*Digest) WriteString(string) (int, error)
    24Ôćĺfunc (*Digest) Sum64() uint64
    25Ôćĺ```
    26Ôćĺ
    27ÔćĺThe package is written with optimized pure Go and also contains even faster
    28Ôćĺassembly implementations for amd64 and arm64. If desired, the `purego` build tag
    29Ôćĺopts into using the Go code even on those architectures.
    30Ôćĺ
    31Ôćĺ[xxHash]: https://xxhash.com/
    32Ôćĺ
    33Ôćĺ## Compatibility
    34Ôćĺ
    35ÔćĺThis package is in a module and the latest code is in version 2 of the module.
    36ÔćĺYou need a version of Go with at least "minimal module compatibility" to use
    37Ôćĺgithub.com/cespare/xxhash/v2:
    38Ôćĺ
    39Ôćĺ* 1.9.7+ for Go 1.9
    40Ôćĺ* 1.10.3+ for Go 1.10
    41Ôćĺ* Go 1.11 or later
    42Ôćĺ
    43ÔćĺI recommend using the latest release of Go.
    44Ôćĺ
    45Ôćĺ## Benchmarks
    46Ôćĺ
    47ÔćĺHere are some quick benchmarks comparing the pure-Go and assembly
    48Ôćĺimplementations of Sum64.
    49Ôćĺ
    50Ôćĺ| input size | purego    | asm       |
    51Ôćĺ| ---------- | --------- | --------- |
    52Ôćĺ| 4 B        |  1.3 GB/s |  1.2 GB/s |
    53Ôćĺ| 16 B       |  2.9 GB/s |  3.5 GB/s |
    54Ôćĺ| 100 B      |  6.9 GB/s |  8.1 GB/s |
    55Ôćĺ| 4 KB       | 11.7 GB/s | 16.7 GB/s |
    56Ôćĺ| 10 MB      | 12.0 GB/s | 17.3 GB/s |
    57Ôćĺ
    58ÔćĺThese numbers were generated on Ubuntu 20.04 with an Intel Xeon Platinum 8252C
    59ÔćĺCPU using the following commands under Go 1.19.2:
    60Ôćĺ
    61Ôćĺ```
    62Ôćĺbenchstat <(go test -tags purego -benchtime 500ms -count 15 -bench 'Sum64$')
    63Ôćĺbenchstat <(go test -benchtime 500ms -count 15 -bench 'Sum64$')
    64Ôćĺ```
    65Ôćĺ
    66Ôćĺ## Projects using this package
    67Ôćĺ
    68Ôćĺ- [InfluxDB](https://github.com/influxdata/influxdb)
    69Ôćĺ- [Prometheus](https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus)
    70Ôćĺ- [VictoriaMetrics](https://github.com/VictoriaMetrics/VictoriaMetrics)
    71Ôćĺ- [FreeCache](https://github.com/coocood/freecache)
    72Ôćĺ- [FastCache](https://github.com/VictoriaMetrics/fastcache)
    73Ôćĺ- [Ristretto](https://github.com/dgraph-io/ristretto)
    74Ôćĺ- [Badger](https://github.com/dgraph-io/badger)
